Package: fmesher
Type: Package
Title: Triangle Meshes and Related Geometry Tools
Version: 0.0.9.9016
Authors@R: c(
  person("Finn", "Lindgren", email = "finn.lindgren@gmail.com",
         role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
         comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5833-2011",
                     "Finn Lindgren wrote the main code")),
  person("Seaton", "Andy", email = "andy.e.seaton@gmail.com",
         role = c("ctb", "cph"),
         comment = "Andy Seaton developed parts of the sf support"),
  person("Suen", "Man Ho", email = "M.H.Suen@sms.ed.ac.uk", role = c("ctb", "cph"),
         comment = "Man Ho Suen contributed features for the integration methods")
  )
Description: Functions that generate planar and spherical triangle meshes,
    computes finite element calculations for 1- and 2-dimensional flat and curved
    manifolds, functions for lines and polygons, and transparent handling of
    crs information and coordinate transformation, including and interoperability
    with sf and sp geometries. Experimental package that will take over these
    features from the INLA and inlabru packages.
